neighborhood_overview:
The Spaarndammerbuurt is a part of the district Amsterdam West. The area is named after the Spaarndammerdijk and – street, which accumulates the northern and eastern boundary.

The construction of the Spaarndammerbuurt started at the end of the 19th century. The streets have been named after places situated in the West and northwest of Amsterdam. The labor houses had especially been intended for the dock workers, who worked in the ports nearby.

The most famous buildings in the Spaarndammerbuurt are designed by Michel de Klerk, who devised labor apartments in the style of the Amsterdam School, situated at the Spaarndammerplantsoen. In the years around 1920, three of his housing blocks got constructed.

The most striking design is 'The Ship’, located along the Zaanstraat. The houses were 'palaces for the workers’, because before no one really cared about the design of the worker’s houses.

Also a post office was part of the block-system. The post

neighborhood_overview:
AMSTERDAM – EASTERN ISLANDS

Where water and modern architecture meet
Surrounded by glistening water on all sides, the Oostelijke Eilanden (Eastern Docklands) are a delight to behold. As the Maritime Museum (Scheepvaartmuseum) recalls the sea pioneers of the past, their adventurous spirits live on in its original modern architecture and historic warehouses repurposed into contemporary hotspots.



AMSTERDAM CENTRUM - CITY CENTER + CANAL DISTRICT
In addition to the world-famous historic Canal Ring, Amsterdam's City Centre district ('Centrum') is home to a host of renowned museums, charming and high-end shopping areas, fantastic culture and entertainment.

Amsterdam’s renowned art and culture and top shopping
In Amsterdam’s centre you will, of course, find the magnificent Canal Ring, but there is so much more besides. The inner city, for instance, is bursting with interesting museums, sometimes hidden behind beautiful canal-side faça

name: Leidsegracht - Souterrain
description:
Look no further! Our apartment located in the heart of the city, with beautiful canals and a historical background, is the perfect location for a movie set or just a weekend getaway. For example, the romantic bench from the popular movie The Fault in Our Stars is right on our doorstep.

You can walk to the Anne Frank House, the Rijksmuseum and the Vondelpark within a few minutes. But Amsterdam's bustling nightlife is also around the corner, with plenty of bars and restaurants within walking distance.
neighborhood_overview: In the heart of Unesco's World Heritage, just behind the Palace on the Dam between Raadhuisstraat and Leidsegracht are the famous 9 Streets. The four main canals are connected by small cross streets. They used to take care of the needs of the rich merchant families on the canals. The street names are still reminiscent of the craft of leatherwork. From the Hauten to the Ree, Beren, Wolven and Hartenstraat. Nowadays you will find the most beautiful boutiques, hippest shops and most special hospitality. But also: a beautiful view of the centuries-old architecture of the Amsterdam canal belt.

name: Comfortabel app. dicht bij Westerpark en Jordaan
description: This comfortable apartment is the perfect starting point for your city trip. Centrally located, you will find a lot of attractions at walking distance. neighborhood_overview:
The apartment is located west of the city center, in the neighborhood "De Baarsjes" on the edge of the beautiful Jordaan.

It offers a great retreat from the busy streets of the city center, but you are not far away: there are plenty of buses and trams nearby to take you anywhere in Amsterdam. In 10 minutes by bike or tram, or 20/30 minutes on foot you are in the middle of the city center (with the Jordaan even closer).

Around the corner there are many cafes, restaurants, bakeries, small shops, a big supermarket and espresso bars. Also, you are within walking distance of both Erasmus Park and Westerpark (with a cinema, restaurants and cafes) and "de Hallen" (with a cinema, shops, eateries, etc.).

If you want to visit the beach you are on the perfect side of Amsterdam: it takes about 45 minutes in total to travel from the apartment to the beach of Zandvoort aan Zee.

neighborhood_overview:
The Jordaan. More tea- & coffee bars, lunchrooms, shops, café's and restaurants available in this neighbourhood than you will be able to visit in a few days. Famous Saturday- (Lindengracht) and Monday (Westermarkt) markets are a few minutes walk away. As well as shopping street Haarlemmerdijk.

Jordaan
The Jordaan is possibly the most famous neighbourhood in the Netherlands. Akin to the reputation enjoyed by London’s Cockneys, this once working-class bastion was renowned for tight community bonds, radical politics and a love for drink and over-the-top sing-a-longs. Gentrification of decades past has attracted more galleries, restaurants, specialty shops and upwardly-mobile residents to its scenic streets but there’s undeniably still a distinct atmosphere to be enjoyed here.

name: Brand New Canal Apartment. King Bed Prime Location
description:
Welcome to our charming Airbnb nestled in the heart of Amsterdam, offering a unique blend of convenience and comfort for up to four guests.

Situated in a prime location, our Airbnb is just around the corner from the tram stop, making it easy to explore the city's attractions.

With high ceilings measuring 3.5 meters high, our Airbnb offers a sense of space and openness. Enjoy the luxury of your own private entrance and bathroom, providing both privacy and convenience during your stay.
neighborhood_overview:
The Rozengracht area in Amsterdam is a vibrant and dynamic neighborhood that offers a perfect blend of historic charm and modern convenience. Located in the Jordaan district, one of Amsterdam's most picturesque and sought-after areas, the Rozengracht is known for its lively atmosphere, diverse eateries, and unique shops.

Staying in a side street off the Rozengracht means you'll experience a quieter, more residential vibe while still being close to the action. The neighborhood boasts a rich history, evident in its beautiful canal houses and narrow streets. You can explore a variety of local boutiques, art galleries, and cozy cafes, each offering a taste of Amsterdam's unique culture.

Food lovers will appreciate the wide range of dining options, from traditional Dutch cuisine to international flavors. The area is also home to several popular markets, including the famous Noordermarkt, where you can find everything from fresh produce to vintage treasures.

description: Enjoy your stay in Amsterdam like a true local. This cozy house is the perfect base for your business trip or city trip. neighborhood_overview:
The house is located in the Plantage neighborhood in the eastern part of the center of Amsterdam. The beautiful green neighborhood is known for its quiet and pleasant atmosphere with historical buildings.

Due to its central location, it is ideal for exploring Amsterdam. Within 0.2 km walking distance of public transport (tram 7) and sights:

- Artis 0.6km (oldest zoo in the Netherlands)
- Hortus botanicus 1.0km (one of the oldest botanical gardens in the world)
- Tropenmuseum 0.5km
- Verzetsmuseum 0.7km

The neighborhood also has a range of cozy cafes, restaurants and shops. You can enjoy a relaxing walk along the streets and experience the vibrant cultural life.
